headline: These Are Stocks You Should Watch in June
summary: Stocks soared in May, boosted by easing trade tensions, solid corporate earnings and signs of economic resilience. Trade and tax policy are likely to remain Wall Street's focus in June.

headline: Is Deckers' Pain Nike's Gain? 1 Wall Street Analyst Thinks So.
summary: Shares of Deckers tumbled after it delivered its earnings report last week, in part due to slowing growth in the Hoka brand.  One analyst believes a resurgent Nike is putting pressure on Hoka.  Nike's sales are still declining, but the business should eventually get back on track.
